OL,3,CHopes that the two child benefit cap
OL,4,Cwill be scrapped
OL,6,FThe manager of a Workington community
OL,7,Fcentre has expressed her hopes that
OL,8,Fthe two child benefit cap will be
OL,9,Flifted in the upcoming budget.
OL,11,FAngela Good from the Moorclose
OL,12,FCommunity Centre says that she has
OL,13,Fseen the effects of the benefit cap,
OL,14,Fwhich have only worsened with recent
OL,15,Fincreases in the cost of living.
OL,17,FThe cap means that many low income
OL,18,Ffamilies receive benefits only for
OL,19,Ftheir first two children, with no
OL,20,Fadditional payments for any further
OL,21,Fchildren.
