OL,3,CHopes that the two child benefit cap
OL,4,Cwill be scrapped
OL,6,FAngela says that the effects of the
OL,7,Fcap were soon felt after its
OL,8,Fintroduction in 2017. Currently, any
OL,9,Fthird or subsequent children born
OL,10,Fafter April 6 2017 is ineligible for
OL,11,Fadditional universal credit or tax
OL,12,Fcredits.
OL,14,F"It made it difficult for new babies
OL,15,Fthat were born, families that had more
OL,16,Fthan two children. It was unfair, it
OL,17,Fwas almost a way to govern how many
OL,18,Fchildren you were expected to have.
